The proof leverages the recursive structure of `unreverse` and the equivalence it maintains with the original game to ensure no move in `unreverse x` is reversible. The two cases (reversible and non-reversible in `x`) are handled by either substituting reversals or retaining the original move, both ensuring no new reversibility is introduced in `unreverse x`. 

